The original problem is a regression problem to predict the size of the area of the fire. We are going to transform it into a classification problem (if a fire is going to happen or not) and hoping to achieve a good indication of a probability of the fire to happen.

First we will transform the orginal continuous variable area into a categorical variable hasFire.

# Transforming column 'area' into column 'hasFire' with values 'No Fire x Fire'
# (min-1, min] => == min => 'No Fire'
# (min, max] => 'Fire

hasFire, y = model.categorise(
    rawScaled.area,
    [boundary['min']-1, boundary['min'], boundary['max']],
    ['No Fire', 'Fire']
)

# areaT = rawScaled.area.transform(lambda x: x > boundary['min'])
# hasFire, _ = areaT.factorize()

x = rawScaled.drop(['area'], axis='columns')

testY = np.argmax(p.test.y.to_numpy(), axis=1)
